<br>
I firmly believe that the uber guilds had an easier time than a_guild_06 that comes along.  Sure, they don't have spoilers and have the learn the strat themselves; however, they have the luxury of doing it.  On most competitive servers, you get one shot at a MOB and if you wipe, another guild is buffed and ready to kill.  Without competition, you can wipe for days on end, learning, refining strat, and still get the kill. It pays to be first.<br>
<br>
Today, on most servers, it's a challenge just to find a MOB that's up that's worth killing. <p>Zaboo Krusher<BR>
