Innate+Y5: 5 (not counting sitting/horse/and only partially counting the use of Y5).<br>
<br>
Total: 70 mana/tick<br>
<br>
CH costs: 316 mana with scm3.<br>
<br>
So, to cast CH every 15 sec (thats an insanely fast CHO) the cleric will be in the hole with 111 mana/15 sec - or 444 mana per min *with* max current AA skills and FT15. With c3 on thats around 10 mins for a well geared cleric. <br>
<br>
To cast once every 20 sec the cleric will last around 18 mins and at 27 sec (insanely slow) the cleric breaks even.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
you math is a tad wrong.  15 sec CHeals = 4 CHeals/min = 316x4 = 1264 mana spent/min<br>
<br>
70 mana regen/tic (1 tic = 6 sec) = 70 x 10 (10 tics in a min) = 700 mana/min regened<br>
<br>
1264 mana spent - 700 mana regened = 564 mana spent/min.  so you could sustane that for just shy of 8 minutes.<br>
<br>
now add to that a normal guild in 3rd or 4th place on the server.  clerics have more like FT2 or 3, minimal AA (usually goes to MGB first), and not always a beastlord or a bard to play mana for clerics and your mana/tick looks more like:<br>
<br>
30-50 mana/tick<br>
<br>
that's turns into 964 - 764 mana spent/min. which is slightly over 4 min to shy of 6 min before going OOM.  this is the situation many guild are facing and why this nerf is going to hurt the slightly lower tier guilds than the very top ones.<br>
<br>
now add to that, these guilds also don't have a mass of clerics in guild that the top guilds do.  they're able to do things with low healers ONLY because of the fact that MODRODs were available.  there was a nice chart i saw on the afterlife board i think that someone added in their modrod essay that showed how having 1 mage chain summoning rod2s is equivelant to having an extra 5 clerics on your raid.  that's HUGE for guild who don't have a multitude of clerics in the guild.<br>
<br>
i have a sneaking suspicion that verrant's &quot;retuning&quot; of mod2 necessary encounters won't even touch velious, as mod2s weren't even in game till SoL and all of velious had been conquered pre-SoL.  I also don't see them doing a whole lot on the encounters they actually deem &quot;requiring of modrods&quot; aside from knocking off 10% of the MOB's HP or slightly lowering it's DPS.<br>
<br>
Like everyone, I will just have to wait and see.  I think it's pretty shitty of them to release this game altering patch a week before a whole new high end expansion.  It's quite clever though, as it will give them their old &quot;we're working on fixing the new expansion and will get around to old stuff later&quot; excuse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showPrevMessage?topicID=2198.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showNextMessage?topicID=2198.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2198.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.emailToFriend?topicID=2198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.threadControl?topicID=2198.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2198.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2198.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpa